                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-417-off2145 t18310908-417-crimeloc2148"></join>. On the 15th of August, between seven and eight o'clock in the evening, a woman told me something was gone from the door - I looked, and missed a parcel; I went out, and took the prisoner four doors off, turning a corner - he had this bundle of towelling, which is mine; he said he picked it up.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BALL. Q.Was it outside your shop? A. Yes; he was not running; I have heard he was in distress.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he had found the property.</p>
